VERSION 1:
Initialized the project structure and configured the development environment, including package.json setup and installation of core dependencies such as Express.

VERSION 2:
Implemented the initial API routing architecture by creating a dedicated routes folder and defining product-related endpoints in productRoutes.

VERSION 3:
Configured the PostgreSQL database connection using environment variables, added a secure .env file, and implemented a centralized database configuration module (db.js).

VERSION 4:
Developed full CRUD controllers for managing the products resource, enabling creation, retrieval, updating, and deletion of records with proper error handling and HTTP status responses.

VERSION 5: 
Implemented a comprehensive middleware layer to enhance security, stability, and maintainability of the API, including request rate limiting, bot traffic detection, secure CORS configuration, centralized error handling, and request logging, ensuring production-ready backend behavior.

VERSION 6:
Initialized the front-end application using Vite and React, configured the project structure, and integrated Tailwind CSS along with DaisyUI for utility-first styling and theme support, establishing a scalable and modern UI foundation.

VERSION 7:
Implemented the core layout components, including a responsive Navbar and a dynamic Theme Selector using Zustand for global state management. Enabled persistent theme switching with localStorage integration and DaisyUI theme configuration, allowing real-time UI customization across the application.

VERSION 8:
Implemented global product state management using Zustand and connected the React frontend to the Express API. Enabled fetching and displaying products in a responsive grid layout, created reusable ProductCard components, and integrated loading states and error handling. Established full client–server communication for retrieving product data in real time.

VERSION 9:
Developed complete product interaction features including Add Product modal, product editing page, and delete functionality. Integrated form state management, toast notifications, and automatic UI updates after CRUD operations. Refined UI styling with DaisyUI theming support, improved modal accessibility and spacing, and ensured consistent design across light and dark themes.

VERSION 10:
Finalized the production-ready release of the application by resolving remaining UI and layout issues on the ProductPage, including improved spacing, responsive alignment, and consistent component styling across all screen sizes and themes. Optimized client–server integration for stable data rendering in production mode and ensured environment variables and API endpoints function correctly after build. Performed full production build of the React frontend and configured the Express server to serve static assets in production, enabling seamless single-page application routing. Conducted final testing of CRUD functionality, state synchronization, and error handling under real deployment conditions. Successfully deployed the application to a live hosting environment, confirming end-to-end functionality, accessibility, and performance stability in a real-world setting.
